`README.md` is the top-level orientation document for this repo: a zero-dependency Rust compiler that turns a fenced steno DSL source (`dict.steno`, workspace root) into Plover dictionaries and nvim LSP snippet tables. It's the map an editor should read before touching any crate file ‚Äî it names the four build artifacts, their producers/consumers, and the binaries that generate them, none of which are otherwise obvious from file names alone.

Key fact: there are two build binaries, not one. `build-dict` produces `out/plain.json` and `out/smart.json` (Plover-consumed stroke‚Üíkeystroke dictionaries, "dumb editor" vs "auto-closing editor" profiles ‚Äî these are two profiles of the same mechanism and load together on-device, so their combined size is the real budget, not either alone). `build-nvim` produces `out/plover-keys.json` (Plover-side sentinel tokens, format `@@‚Ä¶@@`) and `out/snippets.json` (LSP snippet bodies with tabstops, consumed by the `nvim/` plugin). A third binary, `measure`, computes a size matrix and writes nothing. All three read `dict.steno` from the workspace root and write only under `out/`; nothing else in the pipeline writes files ‚Äî an editor should not expect side-effect files elsewhere.

Non-obvious invariant: a stroke collision (same stroke, different resolved value) is a hard build failure ‚Äî the binary prints `ERROR (...): N stroke collision(s)`, exits non-zero, and writes no output file at all (not even the non-colliding artifacts). The corpus currently expands to 6265 strokes with zero collisions; this number will change if `dict.steno` changes and is a sanity check, not an enforced test in this file.

Architectural invariant stated here and load-bearing for the crate layout: one-way dataflow `stroke ‚Üê parse ‚Üê expand ‚Üê {editor, render, snippet, blocks}`, no back-edges ‚Äî a module higher in that chain must never import from one earlier in it. Also: no async, no `unsafe`, no network, hand-rolled JSON (`json_out.rs`) instead of serde, and errors are always typed/propagated, never swallowed ‚Äî callers get a complete result or a typed error, never partial silent output.

Coupling: this README's artifact table and layout section summarize detail that lives authoritatively in `docs/pipeline.md` (passes, module dataflow, error taxonomy, editor model), `docs/steno-format.md` (normative `.steno` syntax), and `docs/porting-notes.md` (TS‚ÜíRust file map) ‚Äî those files, not this one, are where wire-format/pass details should be verified before editing `crates/steno/src/`. `CLAUDE.md` documents a separate context/verification toolchain (`ctx-*` binaries) referenced but not explained here. The whole-workspace CI gate is `bash scripts/ci.sh` (fmt, clippy, doc, deny, machete, rationale, cycle, no-allow) ‚Äî any change should pass this before being considered done, per this file's own instruction.